sql:
SELECT AVG(confidence_level) AS average_confidence_level
FROM frame_data
WHERE subject_id = 123;

external_knowledge:
-surpassed the threshold of adolescence: refers to age > 18; 
-navigating life's journey: a metaphor for the passage of time and aging;
-the most experienced: refers to the oldest subjects, as ordered by age in descending order.

sql:
SELECT age
FROM subjects
ORDER BY age ASC;

SELECT frame_id, AVG(confidence_level) AS average_confidence
FROM frame_data
GROUP BY frame_id;

SELECT subject_name
FROM subjects
WHERE subject_id = 123;

external_knowledge:
Age brackets are categorized as follows: '0-12', '13-18', '19-25', '26-35', '36-45', '46-55', '56+';
Confidence level refers to how certain the system is about the accuracy of the pose estimation;
Pose estimation involves determining the position and orientation of objects, particularly human bodies, in an image or video.

- 'shoulder beacon' refers to the average position of the left shoulder joint;
- 'elbow dip' refers to the minimum position of the left elbow joint;
- 'knee peak' refers to the maximum position of the right knee joint;
- Frames are sorted based on the descending order of their 'shoulder beacon' values;
- Only frames from completed training sessions are considered.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(session_id) AS session_count
FROM sessions
WHERE subject_id = 1;
